ial to military victor. At the end of the first English Civil War, he was poised to take power. Hutton reveals a man who was both genuine in his faith and deliberate in his dishonesty—and uncovers the inner workings of the man who has puzzled biographers for centuries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aHeads of statezGreat BritainvBiography. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / Stuart Era (1603-1714).2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300262759423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300262759.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles